<p>Are there design patterns and best practices for out of process caches with an always on website?</p>  <p>That seems like a common enough situation that folks should not be reinventing the wheel.</p>  <ul> <li>Cache Warmup</li> <li>Maintaining Cache Consistency with persistent data store</li> <li>Recovery from a empty cache</li> <li>Versioning of cached items as new code is deployed</li> </ul>